
\begin{frame}
\frametitle{Initial--boundary value problem (IBVP) for advection}

Advection equation on finite 1D domain:
\[
q_t + uq_x = 0 \qquad {\red a< x < b}, ~~t\geq 0,
\]
with initial data
\[
q(x,0) = \eta(x)\qquad a < x < b.
\]
\vsp
and boundary data at the inflow boundary:
\vsp
If $u>0$, need data at $x=a$:
\[
q(a,t) = g(t), \qquad t\geq 0,
\]
If $u<0$, need data at $x=b$:
\[
q(b,t) = g(t), \qquad t\geq 0,
\]

\end{frame}
